events.name: WordPress Meetup (Mar 2016)
events.description: Talks:  Accelerated Mobile Pages (AMP) (Valentine Chua)A brief overview of Google's Accelerated Mobile Pages project, and what it means for search engine optimisation and your WordPress blog. Community Open Space: bring your WordPress questions and let the community help you with it!  Venue: Amazon Web Services' building management requires you bring a photo ID to exchange for an access card into the building. Please call Jon at[masked] if you have an issue getting to the meetup. Do not abuse the number please :) We're looking for lightning talks! Please let us know if you're interested in speaking.  We're always looking for speakers and volunteers to help with our meetups! Please contact Valentine, Jon or Robert if you're interested in helping out.
events.location: Amazon Web Services Office, Level 10 Capital Square, 23 Church Street, Singapore 049481

events.name: Papers We Love #018
events.description:
Paper #1: Mastering the game of Go with deep neural networks and tree search. (http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v529/n7587/full/nature16961.html) - Michał J. Gajda

Paper #2: "New Directions in Cryptography" (https://www-ee.stanford.edu/~hellman/publications/24.pdf)- Vishnu Prem


-------------------

What was the last paper within the realm of computing/technology you read and loved?

What did it inspire you to build or tinker with? 

Come share the ideas in an awesome academic/research paper with fellow engineers, programmers, and paper-readers. 

Lead a session and show off code that you wrote that implements these ideas or just give us the lowdown about the paper (because of HARD MATH!). Otherwise, just come, listen, and discuss.

-----------------

Original Meetup : http://www.meetup.com/papers-we-love
Papers Repo : https://github.com/papers-we-love/papers-we-love
Code of Conduct : https://github.com/papers-we-love/papers-we-love/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
